FBIS4-57836 "drlat102_c_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-102 Daily Report 24 May 1994 MEXICO Deputies Sign Statement Rejecting Foreign Intervention Deputies Sign Statement Rejecting Foreign Intervention PA2505041894 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 0430 GMT 24 May 94 PA2505041894 Mexico City XEW Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "24 Hours" newscast] [Excerpt] [passage omitted] During today's [23 May] session, all the political parties represented in the Chamber of Deputies signed a political statement regarding foreign observers for the upcoming elections. Felipe Munoz, a deputy for the Institutional Revolutionary Party, read the document. [Begin Munoz recording] In light of recent statements by U.S. Congressmen David Bonior and Robert Torricelli, we hereby reject any attempts by any foreign organizations to intervene in our country's electoral process. [end recording] The chairman of the Chamber of Deputies entertained nominations for citizen advisers at the Federal Electoral Institute.
